Package com.cafean.CalcServer

Class TimestepTable

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.cafean.CalcServer.TimestepTable
  • public class TimestepTable
extends java.lang.Object
    A table of time vs plot file position backed by a binary file containing only time and position pairs stored as double and long.
    Timestep table supports the "segment" concept that is used by some plot files to indicate "regions" of plot data within the indexed file.

    Timestep Table file format version -1.
    Header
    Unused [double]File Format Version [long]Number of Segments [long]
    Segment Header
    Number of Entries [long]
    Table Entry
    Time [double]Plot File Position [long]

    Legacy Timestep Table file format. (versions >= 0)
    Table Entry
    Time [double]Plot File Position [long]

      • getTimeAt

        public double getTimeAt​(int timestep)
                 throws java.io.IOException
        Retrieves the calculation time of the given timestep.

        Note that getTimeAt and getLocAt use a cache such that repeated calls to either with the same timestep number will not require file access.

        Parameters:
        timestep - the step number of the desired time
        Throws:
        java.io.IOException
